trans-unit.source: Contains a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> objects.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo> class allows you to programmatically access and modify tag-prefix information stored in a configuration file.
Tag prefixes associate a "namespace" in ASP.NET with the assemblies and namespaces that must be included for custom controls and user controls to work properly.
<xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo> objects are stored as members of a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixCollection> object.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixCollection> class allows you to programmatically access and modify the `controls` subsection of the `pages` section of a configuration file.
Creates a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixCollection"></xref> class.
The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixCollection.%23ctor%2A> constructor is not intended to be used directly from your code.
It is called by the ASP.NET configuration system.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.PagesSection.Controls%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.PagesSection> class always contains an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixCollection> type.
Use this instance, rather than creating your own.
Adds a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object to the collection.
The collection must not already contain a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo> object with the same property values.
If it does, a <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationException> will be thrown.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object to add to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection.
\- or -
The collection is read-only.
Clears all object from the collection.
Gets the type of the configuration collection.
The <xref href="System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollectionType"></xref> object of the collection.
Gets or sets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object at the specified index location.
This property overwrites the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo> object if it already exists at the specified index; otherwise, a new object is created and added to the collection.
The index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object at the specified index, or `null` if there is no object at that index.
Removes the specified object from the collection.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.TagPrefixInfo"></xref> object in the collection.
